67
00:10:53,441 --> 00:10:57,105
- Oh, yes. Yes, Jeffrey, come on in.
- Thanks.

68
00:11:03,450 --> 00:11:07,613
Well, Jeffrey, you found
something very interesting.

69
00:11:07,703 --> 00:11:11,238
Very interesting. I know you must
be curious to know more.

70
00:11:11,999 --> 00:11:16,494
But I have to ask you not only
not to tell anybody about your find,

71
00:11:16,586 --> 00:11:19,503
but also not to ask more about the case.

72
00:11:19,589 --> 00:11:22,590
One day when it's all sewed up,

73
00:11:22,676 --> 00:11:25,131
I'll let you know all the details.

74
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:27,342
Right now, though, I can't.

75
00:11:27,430 --> 00:11:31,427
I understand.
I'm just real curious, like you said.

76
00:11:32,476 --> 00:11:36,010
I was the same way myself
when I was your age.

77
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:40,518
- That's what got me into this business.
- Must be great.

78
00:11:41,359 --> 00:11:43,435
It's horrible, too.

79
00:11:44,571 --> 00:11:47,689
I'm sorry, Jeffrey.
That's the way it has to be.

80
00:11:47,781 --> 00:11:51,150
Anyway, I know you do understand.

81
00:11:51,243 --> 00:11:52,986
Sure.

82
00:11:56,372 --> 00:12:00,037
- Thanks for the card for Dad.
- You're welcome. Nice to meet you.

83
00:12:00,126 --> 00:12:02,202
You, too.

84
00:12:05,798 --> 00:12:08,881
- Say hello to Sandy for me.
- We will.

85
00:12:09,718 --> 00:12:12,470
- Good night, Jeffrey.
- Good night.

86
00:12:25,316 --> 00:12:28,434
Are you the one that found the ear?

87
00:12:46,584 --> 00:12:49,075
How did you know?

88
00:12:53,007 --> 00:12:55,499
I just know, that's all.

89
00:12:56,135 --> 00:12:59,835
- I remember you from Central.
- Are you a senior?

90
00:12:59,930 --> 00:13:00,961
Yup.

91
00:13:01,055 --> 00:13:03,594
- How is Central these days?
- Terrible.

92
00:13:03,683 --> 00:13:06,517
- I don't know... Boring.
- What else is new!

93
00:13:06,602 --> 00:13:08,678
So what are you doin' now?

94
00:13:08,771 --> 00:13:11,688
I'm home from school.
My father's in the hospital.

95
00:13:11,774 --> 00:13:13,897
- That's too bad.
- Yeah.

96
00:13:13,985 --> 00:13:16,060
What do you know about the ear?

97
00:13:16,153 --> 00:13:19,901
- Didn't Dad say not to talk about it?
- Yeah, but you brought it up.

98
00:13:19,990 --> 00:13:21,400
You know anything?

99
00:13:21,491 --> 00:13:25,323
I don't know much but bits
and pieces. I hear things.

100
00:13:25,412 --> 00:13:27,119
Yeah?

101
00:13:27,204 --> 00:13:31,782
- My room is above my father's office so...
- Above your father's office?

102
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:34,996
- So I heard a few things about the ear.
- Uh-huh. And?

103
00:13:35,087 --> 00:13:39,416
Well... there are a couple of cases
I get mixed up on.

104
00:13:39,507 --> 00:13:42,543
But one name that keeps coming up
is this woman singer.

105
00:13:42,635 --> 00:13:45,920
She lives in an apartment
real close to your house.

106
00:13:46,013 --> 00:13:48,468
Close to the field
where you found the ear.

107
00:13:48,557 --> 00:13:51,392
It's a strange world, isn't it?

108
00:13:52,019 --> 00:13:54,343
- Yeah.
- Where is this apartment?

109
00:13:54,437 --> 00:13:57,271
It's really close by.
That's what's so creepy.

110
00:13:57,357 --> 00:13:59,432
They had her under surveillance,

111
00:13:59,525 --> 00:14:04,733
'cept I don't know what they found out
cos she's not my dad's case. So...

112
00:14:04,822 --> 00:14:07,822
I guess you gotta get
back home pretty soon, huh?

113
00:14:07,907 --> 00:14:09,864
Not really. Why?

114
00:14:09,952 --> 00:14:11,778
Well...

115
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:15,619
- You... wanna see the building.
- Yeah.

116
00:14:15,707 --> 00:14:18,279
- Come on, I'll show you.
- OK.

117
00:14:20,502 --> 00:14:23,172
Hey, baby. Hey, babe.

118
00:14:26,175 --> 00:14:28,961
That's her building right there.

119
00:14:29,218 --> 00:14:32,136
She lives on the seventh floor.

120
00:14:38,685 --> 00:14:40,761
Come on.

121
00:14:54,492 --> 00:14:58,785
So... what are you gonna do
now that you're home?

122
00:14:58,870 --> 00:15:01,575
Help out at my father's hardware store.

123
00:15:01,664 --> 00:15:04,785
They're giving me my own hours,
which is nice.

124
00:15:07,461 --> 00:15:09,833
I used to know a kid that lived there.

125
00:15:09,922 --> 00:15:12,958
Had the biggest tongue in the world.

126
00:15:14,844 --> 00:15:17,084
What happened to him?

127
00:15:18,013 --> 00:15:21,132
I don't know. He moved away.

128
00:15:21,224 --> 00:15:23,797
All my old friends are gone.

129
00:15:29,773 --> 00:15:32,940
- You know the chicken walk?
- What's that?

130
00:15:38,447 --> 00:15:40,524
That's kind of interesting.

131
00:16:00,968 --> 00:16:03,044
Coffee time.

132
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:06,176
Hey, Double Ed, where are the overalls?

133
00:16:06,265 --> 00:16:11,555
They're on the bottom shelf, rolled up,
where they've always been.

134
00:16:11,644 --> 00:16:13,803
Hey, Ed, how many fingers?

135
00:16:14,981 --> 00:16:16,808
Four.

