138
00:16:24,281 --> 00:16:28,230
If you wanna spray for bugs,
Jeffrey, it causes us no pain.

139
00:16:28,826 --> 00:16:30,570
Okey-dokey, Double Ed.

140
00:16:30,662 --> 00:16:33,912
- Oh, it's so good to have you back.
- Yeah, sure.

141
00:16:55,392 --> 00:16:58,096
You hungry or thirsty, or both?

142
00:16:58,979 --> 00:17:03,107
- I don't know.
- I'd like to talk to you about somethin'.

143
00:17:03,817 --> 00:17:06,059
Wait just a minute.

144
00:17:06,986 --> 00:17:10,022
Listen. Don't you guys
dare say anything to Mike.

145
00:17:10,114 --> 00:17:12,819
- Sure.
- It's not what you think, OK?

146
00:17:12,909 --> 00:17:15,613
- Promise?
- Whatever you say.

147
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:22,248
- I don't wanna cause trouble.
- I'm here, aren't I?

148
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,622
- He is nice-lookin'.
- Yeah.

149
00:17:29,464 --> 00:17:31,753
You ever been to Arlene's?

150
00:17:31,842 --> 00:17:33,751
Of course.

151
00:17:46,606 --> 00:17:50,139
Now are you gonna tell me
why we're here?

152
00:17:54,446 --> 00:17:59,191
There are opportunities in life
for gaining knowledge and experience.

153
00:18:00,409 --> 00:18:03,446
Sometimes it's necessary to take a risk.

154
00:18:04,329 --> 00:18:09,074
I'll bet someone could learn a lot
by getting into that woman's apartment.

155
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:12,536
You know, sneak in, hide, and observe.

156
00:18:12,629 --> 00:18:15,998
- Sneak into her apartment?
- Yeah.

157
00:18:16,091 --> 00:18:17,750
Are you crazy?

158
00:18:17,841 --> 00:18:22,171
Jeffrey, she's possibly involved in murder.
This is givin' me the creeps.

159
00:18:22,262 --> 00:18:26,177
Now just settle down.
I have a plan which I think will work.

160
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:30,098
There's very little for you to do,
but I do need your help.

161
00:18:30,186 --> 00:18:32,891
Don't you even wanna hear the plan?

162
00:18:33,523 --> 00:18:37,685
Tell me any plan you want, but it's not
going any further than this diner.

163
00:18:38,819 --> 00:18:40,230
Sandy,

164
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:42,812
don't take that attitude.

165
00:18:45,283 --> 00:18:48,782
All right. The first thing I need
is to get into her apartment

166
00:18:48,869 --> 00:18:52,784
- And open a window to crawl into later.
- How are you gonna do that?

167
00:18:52,874 --> 00:18:57,618
Right out in the car I happen to have
some old overalls and a bug-spraying rig.

168
00:18:58,628 --> 00:19:03,041
I will go to her apartment as a pest-control
man. I will spray her apartment.

169
00:19:03,674 --> 00:19:08,881
You knock on the door, draw her attention
away from me, and I'll jimmy a window.

170
00:19:09,847 --> 00:19:14,508
- And what do I say to her at the door?
- You will be a Jehovah's witness.

171
00:19:14,601 --> 00:19:17,720
I have some Awake!  magazines for you.

172
00:19:18,188 --> 00:19:22,399
I don't need very much time,
just a few seconds. Whaddaya think?

173
00:19:23,568 --> 00:19:25,644
I don't know.

174
00:19:25,736 --> 00:19:31,359
I mean, it sounds like a good daydream,
but... actually doing it's too weird.

175
00:19:32,409 --> 00:19:36,489
- It's too dangerous.
- Sandy, let's just try the first part.

176
00:19:40,875 --> 00:19:42,950
No one will suspect us.

177
00:19:43,043 --> 00:19:48,832
No one would think two people like us
would be crazy enough to do this.

178
00:19:48,924 --> 00:19:50,881
You have a point there.

179
00:20:02,644 --> 00:20:05,431
Give me at least three minutes.

180
00:20:05,522 --> 00:20:10,563
I can stall if it's more, but I need time
to find a good window. All right?

181
00:20:10,652 --> 00:20:12,728
All right.

182
00:20:12,821 --> 00:20:14,896
Let's go.

183
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:29,242
Here I go.

184
00:20:29,836 --> 00:20:31,875
Wait a minute. What's her name?

185
00:20:31,962 --> 00:20:34,797
Oh, brother, Jeffrey.

186
00:20:34,882 --> 00:20:37,883
Dorothy Vallens, seventh floor.

187
00:20:38,552 --> 00:20:42,419
Look on her mailbox
for the number, bright boy.

188
00:20:43,473 --> 00:20:45,549
Thanks.

189
00:20:46,142 --> 00:20:48,846
Dorothy Vallens, seventh floor.

190
00:20:49,395 --> 00:20:52,230
OK. Good luck.

191
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:54,515
Good luck yourself.

192
00:20:55,734 --> 00:20:58,225
Three minutes. No sooner.

193
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:47,576
Yes? What is it?

194
00:22:47,669 --> 00:22:50,752
Pest control. I gotta do your apartment.

195
00:22:52,965 --> 00:22:57,177
- That stuff stinks.
- This is new stuff. There's no smell.

196
00:22:57,261 --> 00:22:59,134
Good.

197
00:23:12,024 --> 00:23:14,597
Just need to do the kitchen.

198
00:23:42,218 --> 00:23:44,887
Grand Central Station.

199
00:23:57,649 --> 00:23:59,724
It's only the bug man.

200
00:24:27,551 --> 00:24:30,041
- That should do it.
- Yeah?

201
00:24:37,601 --> 00:24:39,677
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. What happened?

202
00:24:39,770 --> 00:24:42,806
I was about to go to the door
when that guy did it for me.

203
00:24:42,898 --> 00:24:45,934
- Was it all right?
- Yes and no. Did you recognise him?

204
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:49,725
I only saw his back. I think
he went out a door at the end of the hall.

205
00:24:49,820 --> 00:24:53,402
I didn't get a good look at him either,
but he sure looked at me.

206
00:24:53,490 --> 00:24:57,737
I didn't have time to get a window,
but I found these keys. Nifty, huh?

207
00:24:57,828 --> 00:25:00,400
Yeah, if they open the door.

208
00:25:00,496 --> 00:25:02,240
Yeah.

209
00:25:18,888 --> 00:25:21,509
So, what's next?

210
00:25:22,225 --> 00:25:26,970
- Are you game for more?
- I owe you one since I goofed this one up.

211
00:25:27,062 --> 00:25:31,225
You didn't goof it up.
But... you still owe me one.

212
00:25:37,071 --> 00:25:39,608
I'm gonna try and sneak in tonight.

213
00:25:41,283 --> 00:25:44,118
It's Friday. Do you have a date?

214
00:25:44,202 --> 00:25:47,572
Yeah. I do.

215
00:25:53,461 --> 00:25:56,581
Well, that does that.

216
00:26:10,893 --> 00:26:15,354
- You really wanna do this, don't you?
- I don't want you to get involved.

217
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:18,060
I do, but if something went wrong...

218
00:26:18,151 --> 00:26:21,483
Like you said,
they may be involved in murder.

219
00:26:26,700 --> 00:26:30,115
OK. I'll tell Mike I'm sick.

220
00:26:31,078 --> 00:26:34,661
Just so the record
is kept straight, though,

221
00:26:34,748 --> 00:26:37,037
I love Mike.

222
00:26:38,919 --> 00:26:41,623
What do you want me to do?

223
00:26:44,257 --> 00:26:49,252
First we'll have a really nice dinner. Try
to find out where Dorothy Vallens sings.

224
00:26:49,346 --> 00:26:52,464
I already know.
The Slow Club on Route 7.

225
00:26:52,556 --> 00:26:54,964
Great. I'll pick you up about eight?

226
00:26:55,059 --> 00:26:58,059
Don't pick me up.
My dad might think it's strange.

227
00:26:58,520 --> 00:27:02,564
I'll walk over to your house.
I'll be there at eight o'clock. OK?

228
00:27:02,648 --> 00:27:05,768
You better get out
before someone sees us.

229
00:27:13,533 --> 00:27:15,609
See ya!

230
00:27:40,766 --> 00:27:45,393
Wait. Here's to an interesting
experience, huh?

231
00:27:45,479 --> 00:27:47,555
I'll drink to that.

232
00:27:53,486 --> 00:27:56,772
Man, I like Heineken!
You like Heineken?

233
00:27:56,865 --> 00:28:01,821
- I never really had Heineken before.
- You never had Heineken before?

234
00:28:01,910 --> 00:28:04,401
My dad drinks Bud.

235
00:28:05,289 --> 00:28:08,704
- King of beers.
- Ladies and gentlemen,

236
00:28:08,792 --> 00:28:12,705
the Blue Lady, Miss Dorothy Vallens.

